description.narrative: In 2019, the number of health facilities implementing task-shifting from doctors to paramedics for prevention of mother-to-child transmission increased from 766 in 2018 to 944 (92.5 per cent) in the priority provinces supported by UNICEF and from 321 in 2018 to 608 (74 per cent) in the 13 provinces not funded by the Global Fund. ANC1 coverage increased from 56.5 to 60.7 per cent, screening coverage from 45 to 55 per cent and treatment coverage was 75 per cent in 2018. The proportion of pregnant women living with HIV on ARV treatment was 60.7 per cent (September 2019). | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:09/02/2020
